en_153471_0	Kumar Gunaratnam who had been remanded over the charge of violating immigration and emigration laws was appointed as the organizing secretary of the Frontline Socialist Party yesterday.
en_153471_1	The appointment was announced at the party’s second national general convention held at the Sugathadasa stadium.
en_153471_2	Other appointments made yesterday include Senadheera Gunatilleke as general secretary,Duminda Nagamuwa as propaganda secretary,Chameera Koswatta as administrative secretary, Pubdu Jayagoda as Education Secretary and Wimal Wattuheva  as Finance Secretary.
en_153471_3	The Party Central Committee comprises of 15 persons.
